  help_entry:
    generate: 1
    name: ciarencew.sr-25
    info_sprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 696ae5d39d884004d851eb659e9f5522, type: 3}
    title: KAC SR-25
    description: 'Knight''s Armament Company Stoner Rifle-25

      Capacity: 20
      + 1, 7.62 Nato


      The SR25 is a semi-automatic rifle that was developed
      by Eugene Stoner. It is loosely based on the AR-10, also designed by Stoner,
      whilst still being 60% interchangeable with the AR-15, again, also designed
      by Stoner. The design team aimed to create a rifle that could serve as a designated
      marksman rifle, meaning it could accurately engage targets at ranges beyond
      what a typical infantry rifle could handle. The SR25 was also designed to be
      modular, so that it could be easily adapted to different situations and environments.


      Thanks
      to these qualities, it has been used extensively by both military and law enforcement
      agencies around the world. Its accuracy, reliability, and modular design have
      made it a popular choice for snipers and designated marksmen. It has seen combat
      in a number of conflicts the Afghanistan War, and the Iraq War. In addition
      to military and law enforcement use, the SR25 has also been adopted by some
      civilian shooters for hunting and long-range target shooting.'
    locked_default: 0
    menu_entry_category: 0
  locale_tactics:
    title: KAC SR-25
    description: 'A modded DMR, made by repeatedly banging my head against a wall.

      A
      7.62 Nato DMR designed by Eugene Stoner, and based upon his earlier designs.
      The name is a combination of his initials and the numbers obtained by adding
      those of the AR-10 and AR-15 together.'
  help_entry_generate: 1
  help_entry_name: ciarencew.sr-25
  help_entry_info_sprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 696ae5d39d884004d851eb659e9f5522,
    type: 3}
  help_entry_title: KAC SR-25
  help_entry_description: 'Knight''s Armament Company Stoner Rifle-25

    Capacity:
    20 + 1, 7.62 Nato


    The SR25 is a semi-automatic rifle that was developed
    by Eugene Stoner. It is loosely based on the AR-10, also designed by Stoner,
    whilst still being 60% interchangeable with the AR-15, again, also designed by
    Stoner. The design team aimed to create a rifle that could serve as a designated
    marksman rifle, meaning it could accurately engage targets at ranges beyond what
    a typical infantry rifle could handle. The SR25 was also designed to be modular,
    so that it could be easily adapted to different situations and environments.


    Thanks
    to these qualities, it has been used extensively by both military and law enforcement
    agencies around the world. Its accuracy, reliability, and modular design have
    made it a popular choice for snipers and designated marksmen. It has seen combat
    in a number of conflicts the Afghanistan War, and the Iraq War. In addition to
    military and law enforcement use, the SR25 has also been adopted by some civilian
    shooters for hunting and long-range target shooting.'
  locale_tactics_title: KAC SR-25
  locale_tactics_description: 'A modded DMR, made by repeatedly banging my head against
    a wall.

    A 7.62 Nato DMR designed by Eugene Stoner, and based upon his earlier
    designs. The name is a combination of his initials and the numbers obtained by
    adding those of the AR-10 and AR-15 together.'
